Emacs config. This probably has a fairly ruby bent, with a recent focus on non-html php files.

Snippets from the wild:

Taken from: http://irreal.org/blog/?p=895
(require 'tramp)
(add-to-list 'tramp-default-proxies-alist
             '(nil "\\`root\\'" "/ssh:%h:"))
(add-to-list 'tramp-default-proxies-alist
             '((regexp-quote (system-name)) nil nil))

Then you can edit remote root files with 【Ctrl+x ctrl+f】 /sudo:root@remote-host:<path-to-root-owned-file>.